00:01:09.850 --> 00:01:12.590
to your imagination what Salesforce is. There's a lot of

00:01:12.590 --> 00:01:14.230
things you don't have to worry about when you're coding

00:01:14.230 --> 00:01:17.330
in Salesforce. When you're coding in other languages, there's these

00:01:17.330 --> 00:01:20.240
thing call boilerplate code. Just code that you have to

00:01:20.240 --> 00:01:23.780
write thats thats meaningless, that's totally unreadable. That you have

00:01:23.780 --> 00:01:27.940
to write just so that your code works. In sales force,

